---
description:
Defines the Theme Engine for the LexMastery Flutter application.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Theme Architecture

LexMastery uses a token-driven Theme Engine.

Widgets never consume colors directly.

Widgets consume Theme Extensions.

The Theme Engine is the single source of truth for all visual styling.

---

# Theme Philosophy

The theme is responsible for expressing the LexMastery brand.

It should create an experience that feels:

Professional

Premium

Editorial

Minimal

Academic

Calm

Trustworthy

Elegant

The theme should never feel:

Playful

Cartoonish

Gamified

Busy

Overly decorative

---

# Theme Layers

The visual hierarchy is:

Primitive Tokens

↓

Semantic Tokens

↓

Theme Extensions

↓

Component Themes

↓

Widgets

Widgets must never bypass this hierarchy.

---

# Theme Organization

The app theme is composed of independent theme extensions.

Example:

AppColorTheme

AppTypographyTheme

AppSpacingTheme

AppRadiusTheme

AppElevationTheme

AppMotionTheme

AppBorderTheme

AppIconTheme

AppIllustrationTheme

AppAITheme

Never place everything inside a single ThemeData.

---

# Theme Extensions

Every design category must expose a ThemeExtension.

Example:

context.colors

context.typography

context.spacing

context.radius

context.motion

context.elevation

context.icons

context.ai

Never expose raw Color values.

Never expose primitive values directly.

---

# ThemeData

ThemeData should remain lightweight.

ThemeData configures:

Material3

Brightness

Page Transitions

Typography Bridge

Color Scheme

Theme Extensions

Avoid placing business-specific styling inside ThemeData.

---

# Color Scheme

Material ColorScheme exists only as a compatibility layer.

The application should consume AppColorTheme instead.

Do not build directly against ColorScheme.

---

# Typography

TextTheme should bridge to AppTypographyTheme.

Widgets should access typography through:

context.typography

Never create TextStyle manually inside widgets.

---

# Spacing

All spacing values originate from:

AppSpacingTheme

Never use:

EdgeInsets.all(16)

SizedBox(height: 24)

Padding(12)

Always consume spacing tokens.

Example:

context.spacing.md

---

# Radius

Border radii belong to:

AppRadiusTheme

Never use:

BorderRadius.circular(12)

Always use:

context.radius.card

---

# Elevation

Shadows belong to:

AppElevationTheme

Avoid arbitrary BoxShadows.

Every elevation level should be predefined.

---

# Motion

Animations belong to:

AppMotionTheme

Motion defines:

Duration

Curve

Delay

Spring

Never hardcode animation durations.

---

# Borders

Border styling belongs to:

AppBorderTheme

Examples:

Default Border

Focused Border

Error Border

Disabled Border

---

# Icons

Icon sizing belongs to:

AppIconTheme

Never hardcode icon sizes.

Never hardcode stroke widths.

---

# AI Theme

LexMastery AI has its own visual language.

The AI Theme defines:

Assistant Bubble

User Bubble

Thinking Indicator

Streaming Cursor

Citation Card

Confidence Badge

Suggestion Chip

Legal Reference Card

Reasoning Panel

Voice Indicator

AI widgets must consume AppAITheme.

---

# Component Themes

Reusable components expose their own theme layer.

Examples:

PrimaryButtonTheme

SecondaryButtonTheme

TextFieldTheme

CardTheme

NavigationTheme

DialogTheme

ProgressTheme

QuizTheme

FlashcardTheme

AIMessageTheme

These themes consume semantic tokens.

---

# Dark Mode

Dark Mode overrides Semantic Tokens.

Components should adapt automatically.

Widgets must not know whether the application is in Dark Mode.

---

# Accessibility Themes

Support future accessibility themes.

Examples:

High Contrast

Reduced Motion

Large Text

Institution Branding

Color Blind Modes

The architecture must support these without widget changes.

---

# White Label Support

Future institution branding should override:

Primitive Tokens

Semantic Tokens

Only.

Components remain unchanged.

---

# Theme Access

Preferred:

context.colors

context.spacing

context.typography

context.motion

context.ai

Avoid:

Theme.of(context).colorScheme

Avoid:

Theme.of(context).textTheme

---

# Widget Rules

Widgets should never define appearance.

Widgets request appearance from the Theme Engine.

The Theme Engine decides presentation.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Whenever generating UI:

Never hardcode visual values.

Always use Theme Extensions.

Always consume Design Tokens.

Never bypass the Theme Engine.

Every widget should remain theme-agnostic.

Future redesigns should require changing the theme—not the widgets.